name: tkv2-typed-client-derived
backends: [js]
---

# Toolkit v2 route-derived typed client path-param smoke

This case pins the no-manual-`apiClients:` browser path. The server route is
only metadata for this JS lane; the stubbed `fetch` verifies the derived client
substitutes the single path parameter into the request URL.

```scalascript @side=server
route("GET", "/api/items/:id") { req =>
  Response.text("server-only")
}
```

```javascript
globalThis.fetch = async function(url, init) {
  const seen = String(url) + ":" + String(init && init.method);
  return {
    ok: true,
    status: 200,
    headers: { get: function() { return "application/json"; } },
    text: async function() { return JSON.stringify(seen); }
  };
};
```

```scalascript @side=client
val seen = awaitClient(Api.getApiItemsById("42"))
println("derived-typed-client:" + seen)
```
